      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">49.100</ph> Scope of subpart.</title>
      <body class="- topic/body ">
         <ol id="d2842e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d2869e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
						            This subpart deals with-</p>
               <ol id="d2842e23" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d2869e16">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
								                The authority and responsibility of contracting officers to terminate contracts in whole or in part for the convenience of the Government or for default;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d2869e21">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
								                Duties of the contractor and the contracting officer after issuance of the notice of termination;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d2869e26">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
								                General procedures for the settlement of terminated contracts; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d2869e31">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph>
								                Settlement agreements.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d2869e36">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
						            Additional principles applicable to the termination for convenience and settlement of fixed-price and cost-reimbursement contracts are included in <xref href="Subpart_49.2.dita#FAR_Subpart_49_2"
                        base="i1068330"
                        outputclass="fm:Subparts"
                        class="- topic/xref ">subparts  49.2</xref> and <xref href="Subpart_49.3.dita#FAR_Subpart_49_3"
                        base="i1068185"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">49.3</xref>. Additional principles applicable to the termination of contracts for default are included in <xref href="Subpart_49.4.dita#FAR_Subpart_49_4"
                        base="i1067972"
                        outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                        class="- topic/xref ">subpart  49.4</xref>.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
